Description: Don't install mailq
 Upstream only accepts the "mailq" shortcut to "smtpctl show" for historical
 reasons; the proper way is to use "smtpctl show".
 .
 Administrators who insist on having mailq can create a shell alias, or a
 symlink from mailq to smtpctl.
Author: Ryan Kavanagh <rak@debian.org>
Origin: vendor
Forwarded: not-needed
---
This patch header follows DEP-3: http://dep.debian.net/deps/dep3/
Index: opensmtpd/smtpd/Makefile.am
===================================================================
--- opensmtpd.orig/smtpd/Makefile.am	2013-06-09 20:12:52.217708598 -0400
+++ opensmtpd/smtpd/Makefile.am	2013-06-09 20:14:01.743485670 -0400
@@ -168,9 +168,6 @@
 		echo "$(DESTDIR)$(sysconfdir)/smtpd.conf already exists, install will not overwrite"; \
 	fi
 
-	ln -srf $(DESTDIR)$(sbindir)/smtpctl$(EXEEXT)				\
-		$(DESTDIR)$(bindir)/mailq$(EXEEXT);
-
 	ln -srf $(DESTDIR)$(pkglibexecdir)/makemap$(EXEEXT)			\
 		$(DESTDIR)$(bindir)/newaliases$(EXEEXT);
 
